<section class="about-weapons">
	<details>
		<summary>
			<h2>About Weapons</h2>
		</summary>

		<h3>Bloat Values</h3>
		<p>
			Each weapon class has a predefined multiplier that is used to indicate its relative damage considering its motion values. So the Attack stat seen in-game is a "bloated" version of the weapon's True Base Damage, as detailed below.
		</p>

		<table>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>Weapon</th>
					<th>Bloat Value</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<th>Greatsword</th>
					<td>4.8</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>Hammer</th>
					<td>5.2</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>Lance</th>
					<td>2.3</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>Sword and Shield</th>
					<td>1.4</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="mhg">
					<th>Dual Swords</th>
					<td>1.4</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>Bowgun</th>
					<td>1.2</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>
		</table>

		<h3>Attack Up Buffs</h3>
		<p>
			There are three stages of the Attack Up buff: Small,<span class="mhg"> Medium, and</span> Large<span class="mh1">, and Extra Large</span>.
		</p>
		<table>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<th>Small</th>
					<td class="ta-r">3</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="mh1">
					<th>Large</th>
					<td class="ta-r">5</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="mh1">
					<th>Extra Large</th>
					<td class="ta-r">10</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="mhg">
					<th>Medium</th>
					<td class="ta-r">5</td>
				</tr>
				<tr class="mhg">
					<th>Large</th>
					<td class="ta-r">10</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>
		</table>
		<p>
			Your total Attack Up buff is added to your weapon's True Base Damage before any other calculations.<br/>
			<br/>
			Some Attack Up buffs can stack, while others can't. Per the chart below, anything within the same category cannot stack. E.G. Powercharm [+5], Attack Up Small [+3], Demondrug [+3], and Power Seed [+10] would all stack for a total of +21 True Base Damage. However, Attack Up Small from Dining [+3] and Mega Demondrug [+5] would not stack.
		</p>
		<table>
			<tbody>
