		<h3>Hitzones</h3>
		<p>
			After the Defense Modifier, weapon damage is reduced again by monster hitzones. Each part of a monster resists cutting, blunt, shot, and element damage differently (see the <a href="/bestiary">Bestiary</a>.) These hitzones represent the percent damage the monster will take from the given damage type. Great Sword<span class="mh1"> and</span><span class="mhg">,</span> Sword and Shield<span class="mhg">, and Dual Swords</span> deal Cutting damage; Hammer deals Blunt damage; and Bowgun deals Shot Damage. Lance is a special case: for the purpose of damage calculations, the Lance will compare Cutting and Blunt hitzones and choose the greater (Lance damage is always considered Cutting Damage for all other reasons, E.G. Lance can always cut tails.)
		</p>
